-- New York approves $1.8 billion financing for 3 World Trade Center 
-- 
-- Mon Oct 06, 2014 04:00PM EDT
-- None



NEW YORK, Oct 6 (Reuters) - A New York state development agency has approved up to $1.78 billion in funding for the completion of the stalled 3 World Trade Center building in lower Manhattan.

The New York Liberty Development Corp approved the funding at a board meeting on Monday. The mandate includes over $1.6 billion in tax-exempt Liberty and Recovery Zone Bonds.  It was not clear exactly when the bonds will be sold. A spokesman for developer Larry Silverstein was not reachable for comment. Goldman Sachs is the lead underwriter for the sale.